-elem_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This option specifies on which topology element to configure the route options. The user must pass in this option if the -mode is modify or delete.

DEFAULT

 None

-external_count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

For IxTclProtocol it sets the number of routes in a L3 Route Range.The -external_route_count parameter will be ignored if they are both given.For IxTclNetwork it sets the number of L3 Route Ranges that are createdand will be advertised for external network.

DEFAULT

 None

-external_route_count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

For IxTclProtocol it sets the number of routes in a L3 Route Range.This paramter will be ignored if the -external_router is also given.For IxTclNetwork it sets the the number of router in a L3 Route Rangeand will be advertised for external network.

DEFAULT

1

-external_ip_pfx_len

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

The number of bits in the prefixes to be advertised.

DEFAULT

 None

DEFAULT

 None

-external_ip_step

Supported platforms Details

DEFAULT

 None

NOTES

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

Coded versus functional specification.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

1) The stub and external networks cannot be defined inside a grid. They can added behind a session router.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

2) In modify mode, if IP address related options are modified, such as, stub_ip_start, stub_ip_pfx_len, stub_ip_step, then all the related options need to be specified; otherwise the default settings will be applied.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

3) This function does not support the following return values:key:router.connected_handles <connected_elem_handles>key:router.$row.$col <router_handle>

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

4) DCE ISIS is only supported using old API (IxTclProtocol API).

Coded versus functional specification.

1) The stub and external networks cannot be defined inside a grid. They can added behind a session router.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

2) In modify mode, if IP address related options are modified, such as, stub_ip_start, stub_ip_pfx_len, stub_ip_step, then all the related options need to be specified; otherwise the default settings will be applied.

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork

3) This function does not support the following return values:key:router.connected_handles <connected_elem_handles>key:router.$row.$col <router_handle>

IxOS/IxNetwork-FT and IxNetwork
